  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6568 sitting right between the massive -9042M gamma wall at 6550 and the +5842M positive gamma at 6600, dealers are caught in a critical squeeze zone where they're forced to buy any dip toward 6550 and sell any push toward 6600. The breakout regime confirms dealers are short gamma overall, meaning their hedging flows will amplify moves - particularly dangerous given the cluster of negative gamma strikes below (6550/6500/6540) that could trigger cascading buy programs on any material selloff. Watch 6600 as the key resistance where dealer selling pressure kicks in, while breaks below 6550 could unleash significant upside momentum as dealers chase the move higher.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect violent swings between 6550-6600 with any break triggering sharp directional moves.",
